title: Remember When You Called Me Stupid?
description: Historical documentation of slander. Still cute though.

title: Soup Spoon
description: Still one of the most unhinged pictures you've ever sent me. Absolutely loved it then, still love it now.

title: Pasta
description: One of my favorite memories. Watching you learn and loving every second of it. It was also the first time I realized I don’t have to hate having someone else in the kitchen with me — it just felt normal with you. And it still does.

title: Our Rock
description: Sitting on our rock, looking out at everything and nothing. I can’t wait to take Polaroids of us there.

title: Edmonton Pt. 1
description: One of my all-time favorite photos of us. It makes me so happy to see how happy I am to be with you — and how happy you look to be with me.

title: Edmonton — Car Noms
description: Late breakfast in the Starbucks parking lot, eating Melting Pot leftovers. Top-tier happy vibes.

title: Polaroids
description: A small selection of our Polaroids together. Still my phone background — and probably will be until something manages to beat it.

title: Ranchlands
description: Walking around where you grew up, seeing your old school, reliving those memories together. Getting to show you where my aunt and grandma used to live too. Such a highlight.

title: 7 Months
description: Still feels new. Still feels right.

title: Horseback Riding
description: Being out and about, doing something I absolutely love with someone I love more than anything. Doesn’t really get better than that.

title: Horse
description: It’s you. You’re the horse. Look at those ears.

title: Just Because This Is Cute as Hell
Pond Pt. 1
description: First time seeing a non-domesticated beaver.

title: Fall Out Boy
description: One of my favorite photos — and our first concert together. It was loud, overwhelming, and completely worth it.

title: Just Because This Is Cute as Hell
Pandora
description: One of the many things we match on.

title: Hot Pot
description: One of my all-time favorite places to go with you. It always feels warm, happy, and like home. Just like you.

title: Foot Horrors
description: The beginning of the foot horrors. The very first foot picture I saved from you. Certainly not the last.
